    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "[REDACTED] b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "[unclear] following story of what I observed over the Cascade Mountains,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "as impossible as it may seem, is positively true. I never asked nor wanted",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "any notoriety for just accidently being in the right spot at the right",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "time to observe what I did. I reported something that I know any pilot",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "would have reported. I don't think that in any way my observation was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "due to [unclear] of eye sight or judgment [unclear]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "record for any pilot.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "On June 24th, Tuesday, 1947, I had finished my work for the Central",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "Air Service at Chehalis, Washington, and at about two o'clock I took off",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "from Chehalis, Washington, airport with the intention of going to Yakima,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "Washington. My trip was delayed for an hour to search for a large marine",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "transport that supposedly went down near or around the southwest side of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "Mt. Rainier in the state of Washington. (This transport has been dis-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "covered at the time of this writing--July 29, 1947.)",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "I flew directly toward Mt. Rainier after reaching an altitude of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "about 9,500 feet, which is the approximate elevation of the high plateau",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "from which Mt. Rainier rises. I had made one sweep of this high plateau",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "to the westward, searching all of the various ridges for this marine ship",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "and flew to the west down and near the ridge side of the canyon where",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Ashford, Washington, is located.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "[unclear] looking like the lost ship, I made a",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "300 degree turn to the right and above the little city of Mineral, start-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "ing again toward Mt. Rainier. I climbed back up to an altitude of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "approximately 9,200 feet.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "The air was so smooth that day that it was a real pleasure flying",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "and, as most pilots do when the air is smooth and they are flying at a",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "higher altitude, I trimmed out my airplane in the direction of Yakima,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
